title: Outdoor seating available
text: The farmhouse salad is great. All the vegetables were fresh and the chicken was tasty. I had the low-fat dressing and it was great too. Easy ordering and food was ready quickly. Can sit indoors or outside along the sidewalk.

title: Excellent Pizza
text: The pizza is excellent. The crust is not thin and not thick. It is basically the perfect thickness. The edges of the crust are seasoned and very tasty. The taco pizza is one of the best I have ever had and the twisted pizza was great too. Dining in is an option but the place it is very basic and you have delivery staff coming and going as well as pick ups.

title: Perfect Tour of Tracy Arm Fjord
text: Captain Adam and his deck hand are great guys and made our group feel welcome. The ride down to Tracy Arm Fjord is a couple of hours but it went fast thanks to the conversations and occasional whale, porpoise and sea lion. This outfit took care of us and asked what we wanted to eat, drink and do on the trip. They are flexible and made sure we had a great trip. These folks are one of those rare outfits that is a pleasure to do business with. Absolutely perfect.

title: Efficient Whale Watching Tours
text: This is a very efficient tour. They sell tickets online or in booths near the cruise ship docks. They transport you by bus to the docks and put you on a boat and take you out to the area where the whales are. They then bring you back to the docks and take you by bus to the pick up area near the tour boat docks. It gets cold on the boats and rain gear is a must. The whales are awesome to watch.

title: Excellent Halibut Fish and Chips
text: Nice view of the docks and the giant cruise ships. The Halibut fish and chips were excellent. This place is full of tourists of course but the fish and chips were excellent and the service was great.

title: Interesting experience
text: The food was good but not great. The place is loud and fun. The service is good and the entertainment is worth a visit.

title: Great views
text: Great views from the tram and the top. Interesting movie and presentation from the native presenters.

title: Just a hatchery
text: If there are no salmon coming up the ladder you just see a fishing tank and some exhibits like starfish you can touch.

title: Easy to see Glacier
text: This is an easy glacier to view. You drive up and park and walk to the visitor center or other viewing areas.

title: Worth the walk
text: This waterfall is worth the walk from the visitor center. You can stand at the bottom of the falls and get splashed and misted.

title: Incredible beauty
text: Alaska in general is a beautiful state so I was pleasantly surprised when I found Tracy Arm Fjord to be even more beautiful than the other areas. We saw whales and dolphins on the way there from Juneau and we saw a bear and her cubs on the shore while we were there. The glaciers and waterfalls were incredible and worth the trip. This place is incredible.

title: It is okay but not great
text: The food is okay. Its not bad but not great. There are much better options around Juneau if you are looking for good fish and chips. This is a good option if you just want to grab some seafood without the hassle of getting seated in a restaurant. You sit in an outside tent area and seat yourself.

title: Great Service
text: The service is great and the staff put out special request pizzas in the lunch buffet. The pizza is great and the salad bar was excellent. Great place to get pizza. Lots of seating and relaxed atmosphere.

title: Great breakfast
text: Everything the group ordered was great. The garbage plate is excellent and the coffee was very good. Service was excellent.

title: Great Hotel
text: Very new hotel. Room was quite and I got a great night's sleep. Good breakfast and the lounge was relaxing. Easy to get to via the bus. Bed was comfortable and the shower was nice. Room is new and was very clean.

title: Great place to stay in Athens
text: Great hotel with easy access to the tourists sites in Athens. Parking available under the hotel. Great views of the Acropolis. Could hear traffic from the streets below while trying to go to sleep. Good Breakfast.

title: Nice area
text: This is a nice area to shop and grab a bite to eat. Many cafes to sit and enjoy some relaxation. A few gems in the area to discover such as old churches and interesting neighborhoods.

title: Bring sunscreen
text: Bring sunscreen when visiting the area. Get a guide so you can appreciate the history of where you are standing.

title: Worth a look
text: Take a look, bring some sunscreen or an umbrella. Get a guide otherwise you are just looking at ruins.

title: Must See
text: The ruins are a must see since they tower over Athens. The area is full of people of course and there is no shade so the sun can get very hot on you. I recommend a guide so you get the history otherwise you are just looking at rock.

title: Interesting Ruins
text: Site is full of history, ruins and of course people. It is worth visiting but know that you are going to have to walk a lot and it can get hot in the sun.

title: Large Museum
text: Large museum with lots of exhibits. Well worth a look and is easy to walk to from the Acropolis ruins area.

title: Easy to see
text: The history of the arch is interesting and it is easy enough to walk to or by in Athens. Near shopping and dining areas. Easy mile or so walk from Athens Hilton.

title: Less crowded than other ruins
text: The ruins are the same as most other Greek ruins but the crowds are smaller and the site is compact. Well worth a visit.

title: Small Informative Museum
text: The museum is a must if you are in Delphi. Very good exhibits and nice explanations and history lessons.

title: Greek Ruins
text: The ruins are the same as other areas of Greece. The history is interesting and the views are nice. Two and a half hour drive from Athens but not a bad drive.

title: Walk down the road from the main area to access
text: You have to walk down the sidewalk next to the road to get to this area. It is a bit of a walk but the ruins are interesting and the crowds were smaller.

title: Historical Ruins
text: The history of the site is what makes it worth a visit. The ruins are similar to the rest of the ruins in Greece but the setting makes for great views. It is a 2 and half hour drive from Athens but is an easy drive once you get out of Athens.

title: Wonderful
text: The complex is very interesting and the audio guide allows you to completely understand and appreciate each part of the tour. It is a wonderful tour.

title: Beautiful area near the sea
text: Basically another set of temple ruins in Greece. They are cool but they all tend to look very similar. The difference with this location is that it overlooks the sea and is less crowded and in the countryside.

title: Ancient Ruins
text: The area is easily accessible near the rest of the ruins in Athens. It is worth a look but you either need a guide or some other way to know what you are looking at since the signs are basic.

title: Great Sandwich
text: The Lenwich is a delicious sandwich. The place is a nice cafe/deli. The fries with blue cheese were awesome.

title: Great Breakfast
text: Stopped in for breakfast and glad we did. Food and service was excellent and fast. The price is lower than most other places in New York City and the food is great.

title: Worth a visit
text: Radio City Music Hall is an interesting and historical place. The tour is well worth it. I was amazed.

title: Full of energy
text: Times Square is always crowded and full of energy. With all the lights and signs and people it feels like nowhere else.

title: Busy and crowded
text: Rockefeller Center is very busy and crowded but worth a look around during the holiday season. The tree and ice skating rink are a must see.

title: Small park
text: Worth a visit if they have the ice skating rink open and the holiday market is taking place. Fairly small park otherwise.

title: Nice park
text: It is a nice park in the middle of a busy city. Basically just a relaxing place to get out of the hustle and bustle of the city.

title: Great Soup
text: Great place to grab lunch. The Matzo Ball soup was delicious. The Chicken soup was also very good. Great french fries. Very busy place but the seating was quick. The service was great. Like most restaurants in NYC the prices are high but not as bad as a fancy restaurant.

title: Excellent memorial
text: This is a gut wrenching memorial to the jewish victims of the holocaust. We went at sunset and the memorial was empty and well lit. The statues are haunting and the information is very informative and does an excellent job of explaining the holocaust.

title: Nice tour with interesting boat guide
text: The tour was interesting and we saw a couple of alligators. We also saw some of the homes that people have in the everglades and the boat captain/guide was very interesting and knowledgeable. I think two hours may have been too long since it was hot and the scenery doesn't change that much no matter how much you drive around. The price was also a little high but the communication was excellent and they stayed in touch and helped us find the office.
place: 2-Hour Private Air Boat Tour of the Everglades

title: Interesting And Mysterious
text: The tours are great and this little castle has plenty of interesting creations to consider. The size of the man who designed and built the place makes it hard to understand how he did it. The interesting chairs and tables and planets he created show that he was more skilled than anyone else during his life through today. Worth a visit if unexplained mysteries interest you.

title: Easy and Fun
text: They have a stand right on the beach behind the hotels and you can walk up and book a ride. The staff are very friendly and get you out to the boat quickly. The ride is fun and seems safe.

title: Nice hotel on the beach
text: Stayed in a superior suite which had a little balcony with views of the ocean. The staff were extremely friendly and the room had lots of room. The bed was comfortable with a little noise but not enough to keep me awake. Easy walk to restaurants and shopping. Nice pools and great beach area.
place: Royal Palm South Beach Miami A Tribute Portfolio Resort

title: Great pizza and salads
text: Great pizza that is prepared quickly. The salads are prepared to order and the ingredients are fresh and delicious. The seating is limited but comfortable. Prices are reasonable.

title: Nice beach area restaurant
text: Good food and lively atmosphere. A little loud but the food is tasty and the service is good. You can dine inside or outside.

title: Great Military Museum
text: This is a great military museum. It has tons of guns on display that range from the civil war all the way up to the war on terror. There are a lot of world war 2 guns from both sides. There are German machine guns, US machine guns, British guns and even Soviet guns. There are uniforms from every war. They have tanks outside from the US and Iraq. There is a helicopter inside and submarine exhibits. Tons of things to see and do.

title: Great Cafe
text: Stopped in for a late breakfast and received great food and great friendly service. The eggs, toast and hash browns were excellent and the pancakes were perfect. My coffee never was refilled constantly and never dropped below a half cup. My friends had similar reviews of their sandwiches and smothered hash browns.

title: Informational
text: A lot of information is provided in the center. Unfortunately it is all written in German. Make sure you get the audio guide if you don't speak German. A lot of good pictures of the Nazi history in the area. They don't accept credit cards so bring cash.

title: Beautiful lake
text: The lake is beautiful and you can take a boat ride out across the lake for a low price. The area can get crowded but it is worth a visit.

title: Staff are great
text: I made a mistake with the reservation and reserved a full bed instead of a king bed. We asked if a king bed was available and the person at the front desk took us to another room and asked if it was okay and had our luggage transferred to the new room and keys delivered to us. Great service. The parking is just across the street and was very convenient.

title: Educational
text: The center is very interesting and educational. It was worth the time it took to get through everything.
place: Documentation Center Nazi Party Rally Grounds

title: Walk in history
text: This place is a must see because you get to walk and stand in the same place that the nazis did. If you have seen the footage of their rallies you will recognize this location and it is an eerie feeling to stand their and think of the history of the evil regime that rallied their followers there.

title: Greatlocation
text: The hotel staff were friendly and helpful and gave us great directions and answered all of our questions. The rooms were very nice and made for a great nights sleep. The location made it easy to go to the old town and walk around. There was a movie shown in the park across the street one night which made it even nicer.

title: Lots to see
text: Very crowded when I was there but lots of shops and restaurants. Horse drawn carriages available. It was all too much for me.

title: Great hotel in a great location
text: The location puts you within easy walking distance of the Brandenburg Gate, reichstag, check point Charlie, museum island, etc. the staff are professional and helpful. The junior sweet was incredible and worth the extra cost. I could not imagine a better hotel in Berlin.

title: Great location but...
text: The hotel’s location allows you to walk to your flight in the morning. The rooms are great and quite and new and clean. The only drawback was that the air conditioning would not go below 18 degrees which made the room a little warm for sleeping.

title: Very educational
text: If you are in the area you simply must visit the camp to receive an education on the nazi concentration camps and the horrible acts committed there. The camp provides extensive information and is very educational. It does not compare to auschwitz which is even more horrific.

title: Very popular
text: Very busy McDonald’s but the service was good and food was tasty. Pictures available for non polish speaking visitors. Outside seating available.
